    "body": "the benefit of foundryup as a shell script is that you do not need to have rust on a computer to install, this would be negated \r\n\r\nThe problem with updating foundryup is `FOUNDRYUP_VERSION` is currently used like this:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n FOUNDRYUP_VERSION=${FOUNDRYUP_VERSION-nightly}\r\n  FOUNDRYUP_TAG=$FOUNDRYUP_VERSION\r\n  # Normalize versions (handle channels, versions without v prefix\r\n  if [[ \"$FOUNDRYUP_VERSION\" == \"nightly\" ]]; then\r\n```",
